Since the dawn of history, humans have engaged in structured gameplay. What makes a game competitive and engaging is the clear and obvious rule set. "Cheesing" a level, in colloquial parlance, is to defy the clear intentions of the game creator to the advantage of the player. By breaking the rule-based structure of the game, its competitive viability is threatened, even obliterated. This breaks down the level playing field that brings gaming communities together.

This, in turn, contributes to the social isolation that is plaguing our contemporary society and causes myriad social ills including juvenile delinquincy, premarital sex, marijuana usage, and malaise.
